<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10879&amp;p=123847#p123847"><![CDATA[
The manual of <em>Dr. Mario</em> is about 133.5 mm by 102.6 mm, plus or minus 0.3 mm. If you want to put a lot of information in your manual, consider making it as big as a Super NES or Nintendo 64 game's manual: 117.1 mm by 173.2 mm, same error bounds.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Tue Jan 14, 2014 2:34 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
